</p><p>Matrices to convert to LMS space were not specified by von Kries, but can be derived from CIE color matching functions and LMS color matching functions when the latter are specified; matrices can also be found in reference books.<sup id="cite_ref-Sharma_13-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Sharma-13">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Scaling_camera_RGB">Scaling camera RGB</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Color_balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Scaling camera RGB">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>By Viggiano's measure, and using his model of gaussian camera spectral sensitivities, most camera RGB spaces performed better than either monitor RGB or XYZ.<sup id="cite_ref-Viggiano2004_10-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Viggiano2004-10">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>  If the camera's raw RGB values are known, one may use the 3x3 diagonal matrix:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \left[{\begin{array}{c}R\\G\\B\end{array}}\right]=\left[{\begin{array}{ccc}255/R'_{w}&amp;0&amp;0\\0&amp;255/G'_{w}&amp;0\\0&amp;0&amp;255/B'_{w}\end{array}}\right]\left[{\begin{array}{c}R'\\G'\\B'\end{array}}\right]}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
